The paper deals with algorithmic mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It specifically focuses on designing mechanisms for submodular functions, which are often studied in the context of optimization problems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with budget constraints, which are a key aspect of economic theory and mechanism design (cs.EC).
